the government in public places. In [[Kyiv]], public places were clarified to include parks and streets.<ref name=\"bbc_ua_apr6\">{{cite news |title=\u0423 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0445 - \u0441\u043a\u0440\u0456\u0437\u044c \u043d\u0430 \u0432\u0443\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0456, \u043d\u0430 \u0432'\u0457\u0437\u0434\u0456 \u043c\u0456\u0440\u044f\u0442\u0438\u043c\u0443\u0442\u044c \u0442\u0435\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0443. \u041d\u043e\u0432\u0456 \u043e\u0431\u043c\u0435\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f \u0432 \u041a\u0438\u0454\u0432\u0456 |url=https://www.bbc.com/ukrainian/features-52173584 |date=5 April 2020 |work=BBC Ukraine |language=Ukrainian }}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|US}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|United States]]: On April 6, the [[Centers for Disease Control and Prevention|CDC]] recommended the wearing of non-medical cloth face coverings when in public places.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19) |url=https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/prevent-getting-sick/diy-cloth-face-coverings.html |website=Centers for Disease Control and Prevention |accessdate=9 April 2020 |date=11 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Landsverk|first=Gabby|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/how-to-make-face-mask-at-home-no-sewing-coronavirus-2020-4|title=The CDC released a guide on how to make a face mask without sewing skills. Materials include a bandana, a coffee filter, and hair ties.|date=Apr 7, 2020|work=Business Insider|access-date=April 12, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Since April 17, residents of [[New York (state)|New York]] must wear masks in public.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Ferr\u00e9-Sadurn\u00ed|first=Luis|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/15/nyregion/coronavirus-face-masks-andrew-cuomo.html|title=New York Orders Residents to Wear Masks in Public|date=2020-04-15|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-17|last2=Cramer|first2=Maria|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Uzbekista