ia|Indonesia]]: Citizens were ordered to wear face masks when they leave the house.<ref name=\"mal_apr4\"/>\n* {{flagicon|Israel}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Israel|Israel]]: All residents are asked to wear face masks when in public.<ref>{{cite news |title=Netanyahu tells Israelis to wear masks outside; gives stipends for kids, elderly |url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/netanyahu-tells-israelis-to-wear-masks-outside-gives-stipends-for-kids-elderly/ |work=www.timesofisrael.com}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Italy}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|Italy]]: Regions of [[Lombardy]] and [[Tuscany]] made wearing a face mask compulsory before going out in early April.<ref name=\"it20200406\">{{cite news |url=https://www.ansa.it/english/news/2020/04/06/coronavirus-lombardy-makes-face-masks-compulsory_a852ffdb-a0dd-4c55-a725-e852c5a2fc43.html |title=Coronavirus: Lombardy, Tuscany make face masks compulsory |date=April 6, 2020 |work=ANSA }}</ref>\n*{{flagicon|Ivory Coast}}  Ivory Coast:From April, 26 masks have become compulsory to enter shopping malls or supermarkets in the Southern suburb of Abidjan, [[Marcory]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.connectionivoirienne.net/2020/04/26/cote-divoire-tres-touchee-par-le-covid-19-marcory-rend-le-port-de-masques-obligatoire-dans-les-grandes-surfaces/|title=\u00abTr\u00e8s touch\u00e9e\u00bb par le covid-19, Marcory rend le port de masques obligatoire dans les grandes surfaces|date=16 April 2020|work=Agence Ivoirienne de Presse|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Japan}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Japan|Japan]]: Masks have been widely used by healthy individuals despite absence of official advice to do so.<ref name=\"AutoDW-58\" /> On March 1, prime minister [[Shinzo Abe]] enacted a policy in [[Hokkaido]] instructing manufacturers to sell face masks directly to the government, which would then deliver them to residents.<ref>[https://japan.kantei.go.jp/98_abe/actions/202003/_00001.html \"16th Meeting of 