ban\">{{cite web |url=https://www.malaymail.com/news/malaysia/2020/03/17/minister-bans-malaysia-from-exporting-face-masks/1847543 |title=Minister bans Malaysia from exporting face masks |last=Lim |first=Ida |work=The Malay Mail |date=17 March 2020 |accessdate=12 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319012034/https://www.malaymail.com/news/malaysia/2020/03/17/minister-bans-malaysia-from-exporting-face-masks/1847543 |archive-date=19 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> In April, the government was set to distribute 24.62 million masks, four for each household, while advising people to only use them if they have symptoms.<ref name=\"mal_apr4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-04-08/malaysia-to-give-out-masks-to-households-as-guidance-shifts|title=Malaysia to Give Out Masks to Households as Guidance Shifts |last=Ngui |first=Yantoultra |work=Bloomberg |date=8 April 2020 |accessdate=12 April 2020 }}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Mexico}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Mexico|Mexico]]: From April 17, all Mexico City Metro passengers must wear masks while inside stations and on trains, Mayor [[Claudia Sheinbaum]] announced on April 15.<ref>[https://mexiconewsdaily.com/news/coronavirus/use-of-face-masks-declared-mandatory/ Use of face masks declared mandatory in at least 11 states, Mexico City],<i>Mexico News Daily</i>, 17{{nbsp}}April 2020.</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Mongolia}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Mongolia|Mongolia]]: Wearing a mask is now mandatory while riding public transportation in [[Ulaanbaatar]]. Public officials and news broadcasters had even adopted to wearing masks through press conferences and news broadcasts. <ref>{{Cite news|last=Wilson|first=Brenda|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/breannawilson/2020/03/16/mongolia-announces-3-new-covid-19-cases-totaling-4-how-they-got-coronavirus-precautions-right/#22e676b24fc9|title=Mongolia Announces 3 New COVID-19 Cases, Totaling 4: How They Got Coronavirus Precautions Right|date=Marc