{"title_page": "I'm Jealous (Ike & Tina Turner song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song|name=I'm Jealous|cover=Ike-tina-im-jealous-1961.jpg|type=Single|artist=[[Ike & Tina Turner]]|album=[[The Soul of Ike & Tina Turner]]|B-side=You're My Baby|released=January 1961|format=[[7-inch]] 45 rpm|genre=R&B|label=[[Sue Records]]|writer=[[Ike Turner]], Jane Bossung|producer=Ike Turner|prev_title=[[I Idolize You]]|prev_year=1960|next_title=[[It's Gonna Work Out Fine]]|next_year=1961}}\n\n\"'''I'm Jealous'''\" is a song written by [[Ike Turner]] and Jane Bossung. It was released by R&B duo [[Ike & Tina Turner]] on [[Sue Records]] in January 1961. The record was the third single from the duo's debut album ''[[The Soul of Ike & Tina Turner]]''. \n\n== Critical reception ==\nThe single was chosen as ''[[Cashbox (magazine)|Cash Box]]''<nowiki/>'s Pick of the Week.\n\n''Cash Box'' (February 4, 1961): \"Twosome, having clicked with 'A Fool In Love' and 'I Idolize You,' seem to have their third-in-a-row dual mart'er in 'I'm Jealous.' It\u2019s a shufflin' blueser featuring Tina at her wailing best. Ike's instrumentalists and the gal chorus lend a solid backdrop. The coupler, 'You're My Baby,' is another rhythmic shuffler with loads of appeal.\"<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=February 4, 1961|title=Record Reviews: The Cash Box Pick of the Week|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-All-Music/Cash-Box/60s/1961/CB-1961-02-04.pdf|journal=Cash Box|volume=|pages=8|via=}}</ref>\n\n''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' (January 30, 1961): \"Two solid sides. On top, the gal half of the duo goes it alone on a wonderfully effective [[Gospel music|gospel]]-inspired performance. Much excitement here. The flip features the duo on a good [[blues]]-based ballad. Either side here with an edge to the first. Sides also have pop potential.\"\n\n== Chart performance ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Chart\n!Peak\nposition\n|-\n|[[Bubbling Under Hot 100]]<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=February 27, 1961|title=Bubbling Under The Hot 100|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Billboard/60s/1961/Billboard%201961-02-27.pdf|journal=Billboard|volume=|pages=25|via=}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|117\n|-\n|''Cash Box'' Top 100<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=March 25, 1961|title=The Cash Box Top 100 / Top 50 In R&B Locations|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-All-Music/Cash-Box/60s/1961/CB-1961-03-25.pdf|journal=Cash Box|volume=|pages=4, 39|via=}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|83\n|-\n|''Cash Box'' Top 50 R&B<ref name=\":0\" />\n|align=\"center\"|43\n|}\n\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n{{Ike & Tina Turner}}\n[[Category:1961 singles]]\n[[Category:1961 songs]]\n[[Category:Ike & Tina Turner songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Ike Turner]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Ike Turner]]\n[[Category:Sue Records singles]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song|name=I'm Jealous|cover=Ike-tina-im-jealous-1961.jpg|type=Single|artist=[[Ike & Tina Turner]]|album=[[The Soul of Ike & Tina Turner]]|B-side=You're My Baby|released=January 1961|format=[[7-inch]] 45 rpm|genre=R&B|label=[[Sue Records]]|writer=[[Ike Turner]], Jane Bossung|producer=Ike Turner|prev_title=[[I Idolize You]]|prev_year=1960|next_title=[[It's Gonna Work Out Fine]]|next_year=1961}}\n\n\"'''I'm Jealous'''\" is a song written by [[Ike Turner]] and Jane Bossung. It was released by R&B duo [[Ike & Tina Turner]] on [[Sue Records]] in January 1961. The record was the third single from the duo's debut album ''[[The Soul of Ike & Tina Turner]]''. \n\n== Critical reception ==\nThe single was chosen as ''[[Cashbox (magazine)|Cash Box]]''<nowiki/>'s Pick of the Week.\n\n''Cash Box'' (February 4, 1961): \"Twosome, having clicked with 'A Fool In Love' and 'I Idolize You,' seem to have their third-in-a-row dual mart'er in 'I'm Jealous.' It\u2019s a shufflin' blueser featuring Tina at her wailing best. Ike's instrumentalists and the gal chorus lend a solid backdrop. The coupler, 'You're My Baby,' is another rhythmic shuffler with loads of appeal.\"<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=February 4, 1961|title=Record Reviews: The Cash Box Pick of the Week|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-All-Music/Cash-Box/60s/1961/CB-1961-02-04.pdf|journal=Cash Box|volume=|pages=8|via=}}</ref>\n\n''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' (January 30, 1961): \"Two solid sides. On top, the gal half of the duo goes it alone on a wonderfully effective [[Gospel music|gospel]]-inspired performance. Much excitement here. The flip features the duo on a good [[blues]]-based ballad. Either side here with an edge to the first. Sides also have pop potential.\"\n\n== Chart performance ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Chart\n!Peak\nposition\n|-\n|[[Bubbling Under Hot 100]]<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=February 27, 1961|title=Bubbling Under The Hot 100|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Billboard/60s/1961/Billboard%201961-02-27.pdf|journal=Billboard|volume=|pages=25|via=}}</ref>\n|117\n|-\n|''Cash Box'' Top 100<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=March 25, 1961|title=The Cash Box Top 100 / Top 50 In R&B Locations|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-All-Music/Cash-Box/60s/1961/CB-1961-03-25.pdf|journal=Cash Box|volume=|pages=4, 39|via=}}</ref>\n|83\n|-\n|''Cash Box'' Top 50 R&B<ref name=\":0\" />\n|43\n|}\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n{{Ike & Tina Turner}}\n", "name_user": "Twixister", "label": "safe", "comment": "added categories", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/I%27m_Jealous_(Ike_%26_Tina_Turner_song)"}
